# data-processing-models

Core data models supporting GDPR compliance and privacy management:

## Processing Activity Records (Importance: 95/100)
Models for GDPR Article 30 record keeping:
- Data controller/processor relationships
- Processing purposes and legal bases
- Data categories and subject types
- Retention periods and security measures
- Cross-border transfer tracking
- Third party processor documentation

Location: src/pages/tools-and-assessments/GdprMapper.tsx

## Data Flow Mapping (Importance: 90/100)
Models for tracking data movement:
- Source/destination system mappings
- Data category classification
- Transfer mechanism documentation
- Geographic location tracking
- Processing activity linkage
- Legal basis associations

## Rights Request Management (Importance: 85/100)
Data structures for handling data subject requests:
- Request type categorization
- Identity verification status
- Processing timeline tracking
- Response documentation
- Legal basis validation
- Compliance evidence storage

## Privacy Impact Assessment (Importance: 80/100)
DPIA data models tracking:
- Processing activity scope
- Risk assessment metrics
- Mitigation measures
- Legal compliance validation
- Controller/processor obligations
- Technical safeguards

Location: src/pages/tools-and-assessments/DpiaGenerator.tsx

## Evidence Documentation (Importance: 75/100)
Compliance evidence tracking models:
- Document classification schema
- Regulatory requirement mapping
- Validation timestamps
- Access control records
- Audit trail logging
- Expiration tracking

